D><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">I have the Mithril arms too. They are the only peice of mithril armor I would wear as a warrior. It is the resistance the sells me on them. The Str is nice too.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">PackMan97</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">It all depends on your race. If your a STR starved lil 'un I might consider the arms.<P>I've been hovering around 105 STR for the most part and need all of it I can get, but I much prefer AC. If I did get my hands on the Mith Arms I would probably replace my earrings (currently +4str +2int) with the ac +str and ac +agi ones from MM and Sol A respectively. That would gain me +2 AC, even on the str, +12 hp, +3 agi and +5 magic...which is a nice trade off.<P>The importanat thing to do when upgrading armor is look at everything else you have and decide what you can now afford to replace, as you did with the Jagged Bands. Of course I decided long ago +4str and +10 dex isn't worth the 15AC...so I've been using Jaggies for quite some time now =)<P>------------------<BR>-Alewuf Shinkicker of Povar<BR>Gem Chopper of the 37thRank<P>"Put on your shinkickers and kick some shin!" -me</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">MGonly1</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">I hear a lot about the mithril pieces, what level mobs drop them and where can they be found?<P>Thanks in advance for the information.<P>Warell Twohands<BR>Emerald Warrior 14 cycles on Norrath</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Sulvar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Well in my understanding the mithril arms are worth quite a bit.  If I were you I might take a look at the rest of my equipment and weapons and see if I could trade the arms for something else that I might need more than the arms.  After all while they are nice they don't seem to be a whole lot better than the crafted arms.<P>------------------<BR>Gartuff Little Halfling Warrior<BR>Rarguk Orge Greenblood<BR>Utarn High Priest of Hate<BR><B><A HREF="http://www.handofevil.org" TARGET=_blank>The Hand of Evil</A></B></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Raggrok Skullcrusha</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Bah- I like my indico arms... ac20 +9str +5 dex =)<P>Mithril Arms come off Warlord Skarlon IIRC- lvl 53 Fire Giant.<P><P>------------------<BR>-Raggrok Skullcrusha<P>50th Ogre Warrior; RZ</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Cauldyth</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica"><BR>Mithril is dropped off a couple different mobs.  The breastplate and bracers (neither of which are of much use to a warrior) are dropped off the Kobold Priest and King in Sol B.  They're mid 40th I believe.  The legs and arms are a whole different story.  They're dropped off Warlord Skarlon (legs are common, arms are rare), a 53rd level named Fire Giant deep in Sol B (on the way to Nagafen).  Umm... bring lots of people. =)<P><BR>Cauldyth Arranen<BR>Wood Elf Warrior<BR>Povar<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Milena</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">I've lost the randoms for the mithril arms once and mithril legs once.  The reason I wanted the legs was to trade them straight across for the arms (had it lined up, sigh), because I would wear the arms.  I stood an excellent chance of winning because I was 1 of 3 people who were in on the random.  Oh well.<P>The extra strength would allow me to drop one of my 4 STR 2 INT earrings for an AC earring (diamondine, etc), thus leaving me at the same AC and a bit more strength & sv magic.  The mithril legs I won't wear, it's too large of an AC hit.<P>Milena<BR>44 warrior on prexus</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></td></tr></table> 
